THIS IS THE OLDER VERSION OF FY_ICEWORLD-REDUX v1.0. VERSION 2.0 WILL BE UP LOADED SHORTLY. . .

fy_Ice World - Redux Read Me
-------------------------

CONTENTS

 1.Whats in the .zip file?
 2.Installation
 3.Description
 4.Notes/errors
 5.Author and acknowledgments
-------------------------

1.Whats is the .zip file

 1x ReadMe.txt
 1x IceWorld_redux.bsp map file
-------------------------

2.Installation:
  
      Just place or extract the cstrike folder into your Counter-Strike: Source directory. For    example place the files in these directories: "C:\Program Files/Steam/steamapps/"your user    name"/counter-strike source/cstrike/maps/.../models/...materials/" The "...'s" being each sub folder inside the the main folder tiled "cstrike."
-------------------------

3.Description:

    I spent around, um...I don't know, like 5-6 hours making I think. Its a remix of the classic and SOURCE map called Iceworld. I just wanted to make it a little bit more interesting. I started out not wanting to add so much to it because I wanted to retain the original look but in a more SOURCE kinda way. I started by just making the basic layout but ended up with a hell of a lot more stuff. So, it basically turned in to a rocket silo with four(4) rockets in the middle acting as the original four(4) snowy square pillars that where centered in the middle of the original map Iceworld. The map is square like the previous one expect I added some buildings, a watch tower, a loading dock, the missile silos(obviously)and then I added a lower office level(which is only for appearances and is not enter able.) The lighting is way off, not intolerable but, its just a lot dimmer then I would of like it to have been. Unfortunately, the SDK crashed suddenly on me and the map won't load...at all. Some weird error having to do with "Out of memory loading solid." Yeah, I have no clue what that means ether. Especially since I was just working on a map that dwards this one. Like comparing the Earth to Jupiter! Any ways, this is the reason why I'm uploading this map as of its 25% only completion. Like I said its playable and some what fun. Fast past though, on a count of it being slightly smaller then the original Iceworld version(still getting used to the SDK ya know:)    
-------------------------

4.Notes/errors:

As I said the SDK crashed on me which means the map is DEAD! To explain in more detail..

 a.Lighting is way off

 b.Brushes and textures are not aligned and/or are slightly out of place and size.

 c.The gun placement is a little crowded. I was going to space them out but at least this way its    more cut throat =)
 
 d.There are 8vs8 CT and T spawning's, so there is 16 spawns in all, but the Bots where not given    proper info_nodes, well actually there are no nodes for them to use but they do work because I    did test it out(they bunch up and move together some times though.)

 e.There is most likely a lot more problems with the map then I can even think of right now so I    apologize for this, but the map, as it is is still very playable. So at least try it out and     see what you think of it for your self. 

-------------------------

5.Author and Acknowledgments:

 + Map by: Chase aka ArrogantOrange

 + Rocket Model provided by: PISNORONE 

 + Tutorials and training provided by: 3kliksphilip You can find him and his tutorials on YouTube    at http://www.youtube.com/user/3kliksphilip

 + A big thanx to Valve(obviously)for their great games and the SOURCE SDK(and other versions) 

 + and lastly to the viewers like you who make my learning the SDK possible(yea I did just rip       off PBS:)
-------------------------
-------------------------
-------------------------
-------------------------

Also: PLEASE SEE THE ACCOMPANING .TXT FILE LABLED "Pertaining to the Rocket_silo Model.txt" FOR IMPORTANT INFORMATION PERTAINING TO THE ROCKET_SILO MODEL FILE'S, MATERIAL'S FILE'S AND SO ON!!!!

Details:
Well, here is my remake of Halo 2's Zanzibar. After sitting on this map for months trying to fix the problems with it, i have given up lol. Since so many ppl kept spamming me with requests to finish it (you know who you are), i decided to just release it as is and be done with it. i may recompile it in the future, so feel free to make suggestions here. Known problems: 1 Bad CT spawn, very open and somewhat empty, shadow issues on 3 prob_dynamics, dead water, a few black textures, 1 compile glitch (stairs, t spawn) Specs:
40 spawns, working turrets, spawned weapons and grenades scattered around the map, hidden specialty weapons, buyzones.
Please visit Clan 5k3's studio for more Halo css maps and materials.

Details:
This is a Halo-style map (not a map that appeared in any of the halo games) that features fast gameplay and LOADS of cover. All custom textures, so its a visually fresh map lol. Ive been told it came out very well by those who tested the beta, so i think you will all like it. Specs:
40 spawns, Custom textures, custom Skybox, Buyzones
Please visit Clan 5k3's studio for more Halo css maps and materials.

Details:
This is a Halo-styled map (not a map that appeared in any of the halo games) that features a unique above and below setup, meaning from either spawn a player can either run out the front or sneak under and attack from behind. CT spawns inside a above-ground bunker, while T gets a Forerunner-styled building build into a cliff face. Both sides have lots of cover right outside their spawns. If it wasnt for the above/below setup this would be considered a small map, even smaller than Beaver Creek. This leads to fast gameplay, but can also offer tense periods when one player is hunting for the other. Please note that the spawned weapons are arranged in a Armory, using custom models may cause certain parts to not function as designed. This will not cause any problems with gameplay, it will only make the armory shelve guards stay up instead of dropping down after you have grabbed a weapon. Specs:
32 spawns, custom textures, custom Skybox, Grenade Turret in the CT spawn bunker, doors, blast shields that open and close on the CT spawn bunker, an elevator, buyzones and spawned weapons
Please visit Clan 5k3's studio for more Halo css maps and materials.

Details:
This is my remake of the popular Halo 2 map, Ascension. There are a few problems with this version, due to the above reason (they include a few black textures and a dark T spawn), but the layout, gameplay, and looks aren't impaired at all. There are a few eastereggs to hunt for, and the grav lift/booster works like the original. Specs:
24 spawns, buyzones, spawned weapons, eastereggs, custom textures, animated brushwork, action-triggered sound files.
Please visit Clan 5k3's studio for more Halo css maps and materials.

This map has been in production for some time now. almost 12 months since its conception. With the need of my studio to have a map that they could call their own i created this on a whim. Creed is a mixture of ground fighting with a flare of light from my personal lights rad file. light emitting textures. the layout is in the traditional, buy zone in its center but no guns at spawn for those that want to use the gun game feature. light effects and models are used for most of the eye candy. i have added occluder brushwork to help the f-rates, hint brush work to help the compile time. I must thank Ramaq for continuous ideas. and Lost, Sgt.kickurass for the help in the time it took me to complete this release. The map holds 16 per side. 32 max. This is the Project for Creed
